MoneyBball

Daines

4/24/2021

This project is inspired by Moneyball: The Art of Winning an Unfair Game, a book by Michael Lewis, published in 2003, about the Oakland Athletics baseball team and its general manager Billy Beane. Its focus is the team’s analytical, evidence-based, sabermetric approach to assembling a competitive baseball team despite Oakland’s small budget. (Source: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Moneyball)

Can this be replicated in basketball?

Could data analytics be applied to NBA player statistics to assemble a competitive team on a small budget?

Data Sources

  • NBA Salaries - USA Today Sports - https://hoopshype.com/salaries/
  • NBA Team Salaries - USA Today Sports - https://hoopshype.com/salaries/
  • NBA Players Statistics - NBA.com - https://www.nba.com/stats/players
